# Hard Invariants

These come from CLAUDE.md and override every other directive in this document. They are mechanically enforced. `just check` will fail and block the commit if any are violated.

- **700 LOC per file.** New `.ts` files under `src/` and `tests/` must stay under. Files already over are pinned at their current size by `scripts/check-loc-limit.sh` (decompose along natural seams, never grow).
- **150 LOC per function.** Long functions hide duplication and kill readability. Split before modifying.
- **DRY, no compromise.** Before writing a new function, helper, type, or constant, search for an existing one. If close, refactor to share. Never copy a block "just for this case". Never re-declare a type that already lives somewhere else. A PR that introduces duplication is not complete.
- **Verify before done.** Run `just check && just build && just test` before every commit. Failures block the commit. Never rationalize as "pre-existing".

